  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <title> NOSE_DISCHARGE_case_sheet_part</title>
    <link id="light-styles" rel="stylesheet" href="Case_sheet_styles.css">
    <link id="dark-styles" rel="alternate stylesheet" title="dark" href="Case_sheet_styles_dark.css">
    <script src="https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api"></script>
  </head>
  <body> <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode"> Dark Mode</button>
    <div class="General">
      <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: NASAL DISCHARGE (Rhinorrhea)</h3>
      <!-- S: Site -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Site
          &amp; Laterality</span> <span class="verbal">"Is the discharge coming
          from one side of your nose, or both?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li><b>BILATERAL (Both sides):</b>&nbsp;<span class="infectious"></span></li>
          <ul>
            <li><span class="infectious">Viral URTI (Common Cold)</span>,&nbsp;<span
                class="rheumatic"></span></li>
            <li><span class="rheumatic">Allergic Rhinitis</span></li>
          </ul>
          <li><b>UNILATERAL (One side):</b> <b class="oncology ent emergency">Red
              Flag.</b> Suggests a local cause: </li>
          <ul>
            <li><span class="General">Foreign Body (in children)</span>,&nbsp;<span
                class="oncology"></span></li>
            <li><span class="oncology">Nasal Polyp,&nbsp;</span></li>
            <li><span class="oncology"><b class="oncology">Tumor</b></span>,&nbsp;<span
                class="cns"></span></li>
            <li><span class="cns">CSF Leak</span></li>
          </ul>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset</span>
        <span class="verbal">"When did this start? Did it come on suddenly after
          being around someone who was sick, or with a change in season?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>ACUTE (&lt; 4 weeks):&nbsp;<span class="infectious"></span></li>
          <ul>
            <li><span class="infectious">Viral URTI</span>,&nbsp;<span class="infectious"></span></li>
            <li><span class="infectious">Acute Bacterial Sinusitis</span>, </li>
            <li><span class="rheumatic">Seasonal Allergic Rhinitis</span></li>
          </ul>
          <li>CHRONIC (&gt; 12 weeks):&nbsp;<span class="rheumatic"></span></li>
          <ul>
            <li><span class="rheumatic">Perennial Allergic Rhinitis</span>,&nbsp;<span
                class="ent"></span></li>
            <li><span class="ent">Chronic Rhinosinusitis</span>,&nbsp;<span class="ent"></span></li>
            <li><span class="ent">Vasomotor Rhinitis</span></li>
            <ol>
              <li>ask about spray usage..!</li>
            </ol>
          </ul>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- D: Duration -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>: Duration</span>
        <span class="verbal">"How many days has this been going on for?"</span>
      </li>
      <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>:
          Aggravating &amp; Relieving Factors</span> <span class="verbal">"Does
          anything seem to trigger it, like pollen, dust, or pets? Does anything
          help, like antihistamines?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>AGGRAVATING: </li>
          <ul>
            <li>Pollen, dust mites, </li>
            <li>animal dander, mold (Allergies); </li>
            <li><strong>Temperature </strong>changes, </li>
            <li>strong <strong>odors </strong>(Vasomotor Rhinitis).</li>
            <li>sniffing tobacco</li>
            <li><em>cocaine</em>!</li>
          </ul>
          <li>RELIEVING: </li>
          <ul>
            <li>Antihistamines, </li>
            <li>nasal steroid sprays.</li>
          </ul>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- C: Character (THE KEY DIFFERENTIATOR) -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>:
          Character</span> <span class="verbal">"Can you describe the
          discharge? What color is it, and is it thin and watery or thick?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li><b>Clear &amp; Watery (Profuse):</b>&nbsp;</li>
          <ul>
            <li><b class="rheumatic">Allergic Rhinitis</b>,&nbsp;</li>
            <li><b class="infectious">Viral URTI (early stages)</b>,&nbsp;<span
                class="ent"></span></li>
            <li><span class="ent">Vasomotor Rhinitis</span>, </li>
            <li><b class="cns emergency">CSF Leak (if unilateral &amp; watery)</b></li>
          </ul>
          <li><b>Thick, Purulent (Yellow/Green):</b> </li>
          <ul>
            <li><span class="infectious">bacterial component (e.g., Acute
                Bacterial Sinusitis)</span> but can also be seen in later stages
              of viral cold.</li>
          </ul>
          <li><b>Mucoid (Thick, whitish/clear):</b> Later stages of a cold,
            Chronic Sinusitis.</li>
          <li><b>Bloody (Epistaxis) or Blood-tinged:</b> </li>
          <ul>
            <li>Trauma, </li>
            <li>dryness, </li>
            <li>&nbsp;inflammation, or </li>
            <li><b class="oncology emergency">Red Flag if unilateral</b>.</li>
          </ul>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- R: Radiation -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
          Radiation (of Pain)</span> <span class="verbal">"Do you have any pain
          or pressure in your face, for example in your cheeks or forehead?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="ent infectious">Facial pain/pressure is a key symptom of
            sinusitis.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>:
          Associated Symptoms</span> <span class="verbal">"Along with the runny
          nose, have you had any itching, sneezing, fever, or a sore throat?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li><b>ask other <br>
            </b></li>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Ear</b></li>
            <li><b>Nose <br>
              </b></li>
            <li><b>Throat</b></li>
          </ul>
          <li><b>Difficulty in breathing&nbsp;</b></li>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Nasal polyp</b></li>
            <li><b>one nostril</b></li>
          </ul>
          <li><b>Post nasal drip</b></li>
          <ul>
            <li><b>nasal polyp<br>
              </b></li>
          </ul>
          <li><b>ALLERGIC CLUSTER:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="rheumatic ophthalmology">Itchy eyes, nose, palate, or
                ears</li>
              <li class="rheumatic ent">Sneezing (often in fits)</li>
              <li class="rheumatic ophthalmology">Watery, red eyes (Allergic
                Conjunctivitis)</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><b>VIRAL URTI CLUSTER:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="infectious ent">Sore throat, cough</li>
              <li class="infectious">Malaise, low-grade fever</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><b>ACUTE BACTERIAL SINUSITIS CLUSTER:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="infectious ent">Facial pain or pressure (worse on
                bending forward)</li>
              <li class="infectious ent">Reduced or absent sense of smell
                (Anosmia)</li>
              <li class="infectious ent">Dental pain (upper teeth)</li>
              <li class="infectious">High fever (&gt;38&deg;C)</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
          Progression</span> <span class="verbal">"Has it changed since it
          started? For example, did it start clear and then become thick?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>"Double-sickening" (getting better then suddenly worse) is
            suggestive of secondary bacterial sinusitis.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- P: Pattern -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Pattern</span>
        <span class="verbal">"Is there a pattern to it? For example, is it worse
          at certain times of the year?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>SEASONAL:&nbsp;<span class="rheumatic"></span></li>
          <ul>
            <li><span class="rheumatic">Allergic Rhinitis (pollen).</span></li>
          </ul>
          <li>PERENNIAL (Year-round):&nbsp;<span class="rheumatic"></span></li>
          <ul>
            <li><span class="rheumatic">Allergic Rhinitis (indoor allergens like
                dust mites).</span></li>
          </ul>
          <li>Worse in the morning: </li>
          <ul>
            <li>allergic and </li>
            <li>vasomotor rhinitis.</li>
          </ul>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect
          on Life</span> <span class="verbal">"How has this been affecting you?
          Is it disturbing your sleep or concentration?"</span> </li>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red
          Flags</span> <span class="verbal">"I just need to ask some specific
          questions to make sure we're not missing anything serious."</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="oncology ent emergency"><b>Persistent, unexplained
              unilateral symptoms</b> (discharge, bleeding, or blockage).</li>
          <li class="cns emergency"><b>Clear, watery, unilateral discharge
              following a head injury.</b> (CSF Leak)</li>
          <li class="cns emergency">Cancer sx</li>
          <ul>
            <li class="cns emergency">malignant nasal polyp </li>
          </ul>
          <li class="infectious  emergency"><b>Signs of complicated sinusitis:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="ophthalmology emergency">Periorbital swelling, redness,
                or pain</li>
              <li class="ophthalmology cns emergency">Changes in vision (double
                vision, reduced acuity)</li>
              <li class="cns emergency">Severe headache, altered mental status,
                or neck stiffness</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- S: Scale -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity
          / Bother Scale</span> <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10,
          how much is this runny nose bothering you?"</span> </li>
    </div>
